<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Nineteenth session 
</b>Agenda item 3 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Special Rapporteur on the right to food, Olivier 
De Schutter 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Addendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Mission to Madagascar</b>* 
</p>
<p> <i>Summary</i> 
 This is a report on the mission to Madagascar undertaken by the Special Rapporteur 
on the right to food from 8 to 22 July 2011. Section II (food insecurity situation) describes 
the impact that the recent natural disasters and the political crisis have had on food 
insecurity in the country. Section III (the legal and political framework) describes the 
strategic thrust of the national policy on nutrition. Section IV (food availability) examines 
the public programmes that support the agriculture and livestock farming sectors. Section V 
(food accessibility) looks at land policies, policies on rice (organization of production) and 
fisheries agreements signed with other States. Section VI considers the impact of the 
international sanctions in force at the time of the mission. Recommendations are addressed 
to the Malagasy Government as well as to donors, lenders, international organizations and 
development partners. 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>  
</p>
<p> * The summary of the present report is circulated in all official languages. The report itself, contained 
in the annex to the summary, is circulated in the language of submission and in French only. 
</p>
